LWLR_VectorPrediction - Class in org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.ml.lwlr
WEKA does not make vector predictions, as we typically need it for n-dimensional approximations of transition functions for environment models - to predict a vector of n elements, it is necessary, to build n classifiers for n sets of data sets (see search results for "vector prediction" in the WEKA mailing-list archive).

QFunctionFromValueFunction - Class in org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.tabular
This QFunction has an internal ValueFunction and uses the fact, that Q(s,a) = sum_{s'} p(s'|s,a)(r(s,a,s') + gamma V(s')) Therefore the transition function p(s'|s,a), the reward function r(s,a,s') and the discount factor gamma is needed.
